cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper discusses the construction and application of radio maps for wireless resource management, which is a topic closely related to computer networks and communication (cs.NI). It also involves information theory (cs.IT) in terms of analyzing the spectral activities and propagation channels in wireless networks. The paper also mentions the importance of security in wireless resource management, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Additionally, the use of radio maps for proactive resource provisioning and enabling new applications involves system engineering (cs.SY) and multimedia (cs.MM) technologies.
